channel.title: Jad - Wtf
channel.description:
Well, I was going for a second try for my Firecape on my Main. And well, here look at the pictures.
[img]http://choobisle.no-ip.info:8080/upload/s_Before_Jad_1.JPG[/img]
[img]http://choobisle.no-ip.info:8080/upload/Jad_1.JPG[/img]
Ok, so I was on Jad, I got him to half HP and the Healers came out, I took care of them and just let them go right on attacking me. I kept on with Jad, then all of the sudden, out of no where, comes some Hardcore lag! For like 5-7 seconds, wonderful aye? Well fuck that. It wasn't my computer, because the whole time I was in the cave fighting everything else, I didn't lag once, then I get to Jad, and voila, lag! Yay. Fuck Jagex.
Well, on a side note, obviously I am going to go for it again, tomorrow, it's too late to start another 3 hour journey now.
Good night, Adam

item.title: Jad - Wtf
item.dc:creator: @mod_taharok Taharok
item.description:
@mod_taharok wrote:

[quote=“Mod Adam, post:12, topic:173431”]Um well I’ll post my method, but you guys gotta here this gay shit first…

So there I was… Wave 57 out of 63. I was fighting a level 180, and then all of the sudden, my character logged out. I WAS IN COMBAT! Gah, I’m starting to get pissed off. I’ve randomly lagged, logged out, etc. Lol, more time I have to devote to RuneScape…

EDIT - I’ll post my Method once I actually get the dam thing.[/quote]

Logging out players is Jagex’s version of antilag. It was a newer update in one of the recent engines (at least a month old.)

ninja nub:

And how is it expensive to go to jad? You don’t lost anything…

It is practically impossible to do the second half of the minigame (the entire routine plus the 360 each round) without magic protection prayer. This part lasts a good 90 minutes. After that you have the last to battles which are two 360s and then the jad. These two fights alone take up at least a good 30+ minutes. That is around 120+ minutes of solid prayer and a hell lot of prayer potions. A hell lot of prayer potions = a hell lot of money.

You can also exchange prayer potions and food for super restore potions and sara brews (and optionally purple sweets) to have an almost indefinite chance to get to the jad (if you have 70+ ranged).
